    dc:description "FIGURE 26. Caligus dasyaticus Rangnekar, 1957, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, antenna, post-antennal process and maxillule drawn insitu; C, sternal furca;D, distal marginof exopod ofleg 1; E, exopodof leg 2;F, exopod ofleg 3; G,exopodal segments of leg 4. Scale bars:1.0 mm on A, 200 µmon B,E–G, 100 µm on C, 50 µm on D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1203005/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1203007>
    dc:description "FIGURE 27. Caligus elasmobranchi sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, antenna, post-antennal process and maxillule drawn in situ; C, sternal furca; D, distal margin of exopod of leg 1; E, outer margin spines on exopod of leg 2; F, exopod of leg 3; G, distal part of exopodal segments of leg 4.Scale bars:1.0 mm onA, 200 µm on B,F, G, 250 µm on C, 100 µm on D, E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1203007/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

